reviews.review_text: Sincere Thanks First of would like to say Thanks for providing a source of this show. One of my first tapes was a partial that contained Set II pre drums only, so it is a treat to hear the whole show. The recording is average when stacked up against others from the era, the performance likewise. That said, I still really dig it. Not much to discuss in regards to the first set, decent with some sloppy moments. Enjoyed the Cassidy, Althea and LIG. All these years later, I still love the pre drums Set II, especially the beautiful To Lay Me Down. Thanks again, gentlemen.

VG show I have to say that I think this show is very good. The first set is just pulsing with energy. The second set becomes a bit more human but, on balance is very good, and has passages of excellence.

...my $.02.....
Portland This show demonstrates how ‘81 was a fantastic year. This was the last peak this high. The Berkeley shows are at the very top for the Brent years.
Pretty Damn Good 2nd of 3 show run. Seattle smoked and this show was not as wired, but pretty damn good.
